Delicious salvadorian food!!! I highly recommend! A must go to place. Authentic food, from the beans to the fajitas to the Pupusas. Great service, great ambiance! The fiesta platter has a bit of everything, if you're undecided on what to eat. Must try!!!

Unfortunately this place has really gone down hill. The food is inexpensive, wait staff is charming and location is great. But the quality of food is pretty much as low as it gets. The salsa is straight out of a can or jar. Same thing for cheese sauce with chips. They use the cheapest cheese sauce that you get out of a can from the grocery story and it’s served cold. The enchiladas don’t have red sauce (or any sauce). I understand many restaurants are struggling during covid and I want to be supportive, but if they try to save costs by serving the cheapest food possible- people are going to stop coming and look elsewhere. It’s sad to see.

Based on this we decided not to order entrees and just had an appetizer of taquitos to tide us over while we found a different restaurant. The advertised "fresh guacamole" was clearly nothing of the sort. The menu offered generic tex mex and we left without ordering anything else. Extremely disappointed.
